    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-11T15:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-11T15:30:00-05:00" n="220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/3530: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-11T18:00:00-02:30"
                            >January 11, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Uruguayan Foreign Office states it has been approached by local Jewish
                    committee with request to permit entry into Uruguay of several hundred Jewish
                    refugee children, the committee claiming that the United States Government has
                    acceded to a similar request made by Jewish committees in the United States.
                    Foreign Office would appreciate confirmation of above before taking action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
